rom greatness. (Shannon L. Alder)\nRemembering that you are going to die is the best way I know to avoid the trap of thinking you have something to lose. You are already naked. There is no reason not to follow your heart. (Steve Jobs)\nTruth is stranger than fiction, but it is because Fiction is obliged to stick to possibilities; Truth isn\'t. (Mark Twain)\nYou’ve got about as much charm as a dead slug. (Suzanne Collins)\nYou haven\'t got a letter on yours,\" George observed. \"I suppose she thinks you don\'t forget your name. But we\'re not stupid-we know we\'re called Gred and Forge. (J.K. Rowling)', '2022-07-08 21:18:40', 0),
