(843, 'He’s not perfect. You aren’t either, and the two of you will never be perfect. But if he can make you laugh at least once, causes you to think twice, and if he admits to being human and making mistakes, hold onto him and give him the most you can. He isn’t going to quote poetry, he’s not thinking about you every moment, but he will give you a part of him that he knows you could break. Don’t hurt him, don’t change him, and don’t expect for more than he can give. Don’t analyze. Smile when he makes you happy, yell when he makes you mad, and miss him when he’s not there. Love hard when there is love to be had. Because perfect guys don’t exist, but there’s always one guy that is perfect for you. (Bob Marley)\nLove does not begin and end the way we seem to think it does. Love is a battle, love is a war; love is a growing up. (James A. Baldwin)\nAnd when her lips met mine, I knew that I could live to be a hundred and visit every country in the world, but nothing would ever compare to that single moment when I first kissed the girl of my dreams and knew that my love would last forever. (Nicholas Sparks)\nLearn from the mistakes of others. You can never live long enough to make them all yourself. (Groucho Marx)\nDress shabbily and they remember the dress; dress impeccably and they remember the woman. (Coco Chanel)\nAsk not what you can do for your country. Ask what’s for lunch. (Orson Welles)\nWe do not need magic to transform our world. We carry all the power we need inside ourselves already. (J.K. Rowling)\nAngry, and half in love with her, and tremendously sorry, I turned away. (F. Scott Fitzgerald)\nYou haven\'t got a letter on yours,\" George observed. \"I suppose she thinks you don\'t forget your name. But we\'re not stupid-we know we\'re called Gred and Forge. (J.K. Rowling)\nIf you want to keep a secret, you must also hide it from yourself. (George Orwell)', '2022-07-08 21:18:41', 0),
