(907, 'You’ll get over it… (Jeanette Winterson)\nLet everything happen to youBeauty and terrorJust keep goingNo feeling is final (Rainer Maria Rilke)\nThe very essence of romance is uncertainty. (Oscar Wilde)\nBut I love your feet only because they walked upon the earth and upon the wind and upon the waters, until they found me. (Pablo Neruda)\nDo not think that love in order to be genuine has to be extraordinary. What we need is to love without getting tired. Be faithful in small things because it is in them that your strength lies. (Mother Teresa)\nIf he’s not calling you, it’s because you are not on his mind. If he creates expectations for you, and then doesn’t follow through on little things, he will do same for big things. Be aware of this and realize that he’s okay with disappointing you. Don’t be with someone who doesn’t do what they say they’re going to do. If he’s choosing not to make a simple effort that would put you at ease and bring harmony to a recurring fight, then he doesn’t respect your feelings and needs. “Busy,asshole.,Asshole (Greg Behrendt)\nI\'m not saying that everything is survivable. Just that everything except the last thing is. (John Green)\nDid you see that dress? (Richelle Mead)\nIt is not a lack of love, but a lack of friendship that makes unhappy marriages. (Friedrich Nietzsche)\nIn your light I learn how to love. In your beauty, how to make poems. You dance inside my chest where no-one sees you, but sometimes I do, and that sight becomes this art. (Rumi)', '2022-07-08 21:18:41', 0),
