(920, 'Some things in life are out of your control. You can make it a party or a tragedy. (Nora Roberts)\nTis better to have loved and lostThan never to have loved at all. (Alfred Lord Tennyson)\nIt is a truth universally acknowledged, that a single man in possession of a good fortune, must be in want of a wife. (Jane Austen)\nDon\'t think or judge, just listen. (Sarah Dessen)\nI am not proud, but I am happy; and happiness blinds, I think, more than pride. (Alexandre Dumas)\nBe clearly aware of the stars and infinity on high. Then life seems almost enchanted after all. (Vincent Van Gogh)\nI\'ve got the guts to die. What I want to know is, have you got the guts to live? (Tennessee Williams)\nI am an excitable person who only understands life lyrically, musically, in whom feelings are much stronger as reason. I am so thirsty for the marvelous that only the marvelous has power over me. Anything I can not transform into something marvelous, I let go. Reality doesn\'t impress me. I only believe in intoxication, in ecstasy, and when ordinary life shackles me, I escape, one way or another. No more walls. (Anais Nin)\nEvery day is a new day. It is better to be lucky. But I would rather be exact. Then when luck comes you are ready. (Ernest Hemingway)\nLearn from the mistakes of others. You can never live long enough to make them all yourself. (Groucho Marx)', '2022-07-08 21:18:41', 0),
(921, 'And I asked myself about the present: how wide it was, how deep it was, how much was mine to keep. (Kurt Vonnegut)\nI read so I can live more than one life in more than one place. (Anne Tyler)\nFinish each day and be done with it. You have done what you could. Some blunders and absurdities no doubt crept in; forget them as soon as you can. Tomorrow is a new day. You shall begin it serenely and with too high a spirit to be encumbered with your old nonsense. (Ralph Waldo Emerson)\nDon’t go around saying the world owes you a living. The world owes you nothing. It was here first. (Mark Twain)\nHow wrong is it for a woman to expect the man to build the world she wants, rather than to create it herself? (Anais Nin)\nThough my soul may set in darkness, it will rise in perfect light; I have loved the stars too fondly to be fearful of the night. (Sarah   Williams)\nWe can\'t be afraid of change. You may feel very secure in the pond that you are in, but if you never venture out of it, you will never know that there is such a thing as an ocean, a sea. Holding onto something that is good for you now, may be the very reason why you don\'t have something better. (C. JoyBell C.)\nLet no one ever come to you without leaving better and happier. Be the living expression of God\'s kindness: kindness in your face, kindness in your eyes, kindness in your smile. (Mother Teresa)\nWe loved with a love that was more than love. (Edgar Allen Poe)\n...you can hate a place with all your heart and soul and still be homesick for it. (Joseph Mitchell)', '2022-07-08 21:18:41', 0);
