(963, 'A brave man acknowledges the strength of others. (Veronica Roth)\nThe more I read, the more I acquire, the more certain I am that I know nothing. (Voltaire)\nI decided as long as I\'m going to hell, I might as well do it thoroughly. (Stephenie Meyer)\nMany boys will bring you flowers. But someday you\'ll meet a boy who will learn your favorite flower, your favorite song, your favorite sweet. And even if he is too poor to give you any of them, it won\'t matter because he will have taken the time to know you as no one else does. Only that boy earns your heart. (Leigh Bardugo)\nOf course it is happening inside your head, Harry, but why on earth should that mean that it is not real? (J.K. Rowling)\nI shut my eyes and all the world drops dead; I lift my eyes and all is born again. (Sylvia Plath)\nI don\'t like people who have never fallen or stumbled. Their virtue is lifeless and it isn\'t of much value. Life hasn\'t revealed its beauty to them.  (Boris Pasternak)\nThe greatness of a nation and its moral progress can be judged by the way its animals are treated. (Mahatma Gandhi)\nI guess that\'s what saying good-bye is always like--like jumping off an edge. The worst part is making the choice to do it. Once you\'re in the air, there\'s nothing you can do but let go. (Lauren Oliver)\nFantasy is a necessary ingredient in living, it\'s a way of looking at life through the wrong end of a telescope. (Dr. Seuss)', '2022-07-08 21:18:41', 0),
